<RelativeLayout xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    xmlns:tools="http://schemas.android.com/tools"
    android:id="@+id/container"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent"
    tools:context="afoofaGeneralGeometry.general_geometry.Bsquare"
    tools:ignore="MergeRootFrame" >

    <ScrollView
        android:id="@+id/scrollv"
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"

        >

        <LinearLayout
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:orientation="vertical" >


            <ImageView
                android:id="@+id/imageView1"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_gravity="center"
                android:layout_marginTop="17dp"
                android:src="@drawable/squares"  />

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/textView3"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_alignParentLeft="true"
                android:layout_centerVertical="true"
                android:fontFamily="monospace"
                android:layout_marginLeft="10dp"
                android:layout_marginTop="20dp"
                android:textSize="20sp"
                android:text="Definition:"/>
            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/textView2"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_alignParentLeft="true"
                android:layout_centerVertical="true"
                android:layout_margin="10dp"
                android:textSize="18sp"
                android:text="A 4-sided regular polygon with all sides equal and all internal angles 90°
\n
The square is probably the best known of the quadrilaterals. It is defined as having all sides equal, and its interior angles all right angles (90°). From this it follows that the opposite sides are also parallel.
\n
A square is simply a specific case of a regular polygon, in this case with 4 sides. All the facts and properties described for regular polygons apply to a square.\n"/>

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/textView4"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_alignParentLeft="true"
                android:layout_centerVertical="true"
                android:fontFamily="monospace"
                android:layout_marginLeft="10dp"
                android:layout_marginTop="20dp"
                android:textSize="20sp"
                android:text="Formulas:\n"/>
            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/textView5"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_alignParentLeft="true"
                android:layout_centerVertical="true"
                android:layout_margin="10dp"
                android:textSize="18sp"
                android:textStyle="bold"
                android:textColor="@color/purple"
                android:text="perimeter: \n   4s\n\n area:\n    s2"/>

            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="5dp"
                android:layout_marginLeft="15dp"
                android:layout_marginBottom="10dp"
                android:text="s is side of square."
                />

        </LinearLayout>
    </ScrollView>
</RelativeLayout>



